The blaze destroyed five shacks on Friday, leaving 18 people without a home. Among those killed in the fire were a man, a woman, and three children. CAPE TOWN The cause of a fire which claimed the lives of a family of five in Nomzamo, near Strand is yet to be determined.The blaze destroyed five shacks on Friday, leaving 18 people without a home.Among those killed in the fire were a man, a woman, and three children.The police s Andre Traut says, The death of family of five are being investigated after they succumbed to the fire at their residence at approximately 6 o clock. A inquest docket has been registered. 